---

## Step 3

Explain the HashMap.

> "The sorted string acts as the key, while the value is a list containing all original words sharing that key."

---

## Step 4

Explain the algorithm.

> "I iterate through each word, sort it, generate its canonical representation, and use that as the HashMap key. If the key already exists, I append the word to the corresponding list; otherwise, I create a new list. Finally, I return all the grouped lists."

