# Common Follow-up Questions

## Q1. Why use the sorted string as the key?

Because every anagram has the same sorted representation.

---

## Q2. Why not use the original string as the key?

The original strings are different (`"eat"` and `"tea"`), so they would not be grouped together.

---

## Q3. Can this be optimized further?

Yes.

Instead of sorting, create a frequency count of the 26 lowercase letters and use that frequency representation as the key.

This avoids sorting and can improve performance for longer strings.

---

# Mistakes to Avoid

❌ Using the original string as the HashMap key.

✅ Use the sorted string (canonical representation).

---

❌ Forgetting to create a new list for a new key.

✅ Check `containsKey()` before adding.

---

❌ Saying the time complexity is `O(n)`.

✅ Sorting each string costs `O(k log k)`, so the total is `O(n × k log k)`.

