# Interview Summary (30 Seconds)

> "I recognize this as a HashMap grouping problem. The key observation is that all anagrams have the same sorted representation. I iterate through each string, sort its characters to generate a canonical key, and use that key in a `HashMap<String, List<String>>`. If the key already exists, I append the current word to its list; otherwise, I create a new list. Finally, I return all the lists stored in the map. The overall time complexity is `O(n × k log k)` because each string of length `k` is sorted, and the space complexity is `O(n × k)`."

